27/05/2007
ATHENS, Greece -- Flooding has killed five people and three others are missing in southern Greece, according to media reports Sunday (May 27th).
The Lousios River, in the Peloponnese region, swamped its banks, sweeping away eight members of a hiking group as they tried to cross the river Saturday.
Ten others managed to escape.
(Focus, AP, Darik - 27/05/07)
